A physiotherapist, Mrs Lola Jude, has advised stroke patients on the need for regular rehabilitation therapy to prevent further deformities. She gave the advice in an interview with News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Thursday in Abuja. According to her, patients need constant attention to prevent their bodies from becoming stiff.   Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The NEWS. Click here to read the full text on the original website.